The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Rooted in reality
  Colour and imagination, reality and society are inseparable parts of an artists canvas. In fact, creative art is more than just a splash of colours. These colours are the essence of an artists impulse for reordering reality  a reality discoloured by hatred, sadism and death consciousness. The artists of Assam with a passion imbibed from nature, are deft exponents of colours voicing the inner silence of men. The unspoken pathos, the sense of utter helplessness and the continuous fight against day-to-day drudgery are portrayed in their canvases. It is perhaps one of the unique combinations of emotions and colours. Assam Fine Arts and Crafts Society, Guwahati showcases works of some of Assams leading artists. When: Till today; 3 pm - 8 pmWhere: Academy of Fine  Copyright 
